WEBVTT

00:03:28.001 --> 00:03:30.331
And I was a huge, huge
believer in the company.

00:03:30.355 --> 00:03:35.363
And when I retired from the business
at the end of 2015,

00:03:35.387 --> 00:03:38.561
and I started to see things going wrong,

00:03:38.585 --> 00:03:42.663
I was shocked because I really thought
Facebook, at its core,

00:03:42.687 --> 00:03:45.036
had a better value system,

00:03:45.060 --> 00:03:48.949
and that the product was designed to be,

00:03:48.973 --> 00:03:52.233
you know, both fun
and, at least, not harmful.

00:03:52.257 --> 00:03:55.170
CA: What was the first thing
that gave you pause for thought?

00:03:55.194 --> 00:03:57.487
RM: There were two
that happened right in a row.

00:03:57.511 --> 00:04:00.632
The first was during the 2016
Democratic primary in New Hampshire,